Consumed by LÖVE's love.font (src/modules/font/freetype: TrueTypeRasterizer,
HarfbuzzShaper) per readme.md's build map ("vendored from outside: FreeType").

SUBSET — what is vendored and why:
  include/         verbatim, whole (headers cross-reference).
  src/base         core objects + the base tools LÖVE calls (ftbbox, ftbitmap,
                   ftglyph, ftstroke, ftgasp, ftmm, ftsynth, ftsystem, ftinit,
                   ftdebug, ftbase).
  src/{sfnt,truetype,cff}      TrueType + OpenType/CFF font drivers.
  src/{psnames,pshinter,psaux} PostScript name/hinting/aux for CFF.
  src/autofit      the auto-hinter.
  src/{smooth,raster}          the anti-aliased + monochrome rasterizers.
  Dropped: bdf, pcf, pfr, type1, cid, type42, winfonts, gxvalid, otvalid,
  svg, sdf, cache, bzip2, lzw, gzip, dlg, tools — none needed for TTF/OTF.

BUILD CONFIG (ours, in wasi-config/, applied via -DFT_CONFIG_OPTIONS_H /
-DFT_CONFIG_MODULES_H so upstream source is never edited in place):
  ftmodule.h  the module list matching the compiled subset.
  ftoption.h  stock upstream, with FT_CONFIG_OPTION_USE_ZLIB disabled (no
              gzip/WOFF → no second bundled zlib; wasi/vendor/zlib is the one
              zlib). To add WOFF later: re-enable USE_ZLIB + define
              FT_CONFIG_OPTION_SYSTEM_ZLIB and link wasi/vendor/zlib.

FreeType uses setjmp/longjmp (smooth/ftgrays.c, sfnt/ttcmap.c), which the apt
wasi-libc omits; it links the sysroot's wasm setjmp support (wasi/toolchain/
setjmp), so its TUs compile with $EH_FLAGS $SJLJ_FLAGS. Built to a static
archive by build.sh; witnessed by run.sh (renders glyph 'A' from Vera.ttf in
node + Chromium + wasmtime). Update by re-dropping the subset from a newer
release and refreshing this PIN. Never edit upstream files in place.
